How does npm behave differently with ignore-scripts set to true?

If you want to be safe, use '--ignore-scripts' or the config setting, but also use can-i-ignore-scripts. It helps you find out which scripts exist (especially when you install new dependencies), but prevents automatically executing new scripts which appear with a new version of a library you already use.
